t and translation contents provided by the Company are complete and accurate and useful for the user, and that any original text and translation contents provided by the Company satisfy purposes of the user to use the Service, including personal and non-profit use by the user (hereinafter referred to as “personal use”).2 Since text-to-speech in this Service is by voice-synthesis software, the User may have difficulty hearing the pronunciation and intonation, or there may be mistakes, the user shall use the Service at his/her own risk upon consenting to this..Article 6 (Disclaimer).The Company, the Service or the developer of the software which is incorporated in the Service shall not be liable for any responsibility for any damage caused to the User or third party by using this Service..Article 7 (Prohibited Matters).If the Company determines that the User falls under any of the following articles, the Company may stop or suspend the use of the Service without notifying the User in advance: If the User or the third party suffers a loss due to the violation of the Terms, the User shall bear all costs, and the Company shall not be liable for the loss at all..(1) Acts to use the original text and translation contents of the Service by exceeding the scope of private use or acts to use the Service by publicly announcing, quoting or modifying the original text and translation contents of the Service.(2) Acts to produce or sell a website using the Service by exceeding the scope of private use.(3) Acts to develop an illegitimate tool or function by using the Service which the Company does not approve.(4) Acts to quote the original text and translation contents of the Service on the software developed by the third party that is not approved by the Company (referring to a corporation or an individual, regardless of a commercial or non-profit).(5) Acts that violate the Terms or rules of the Service indicated on the Service, regardless of its name, or acts that are likely to violate the Terms or the rules of the Service.(6) Acts that violate the laws, guidelines, rules, etc., or acts that are likely to violate the laws, guidelines, rules, etc.(7) Acts to use intellectual property rights, such as copyright, trademark rights, etc. used on the Service without the written prior consent of the Company or other right holders, or acts to apply for registration, etc. for those rights.(8) Acts to disturb the smooth operation of the Service with virus program and unauthorized access.(9) Directly seeking money and other commercial interests by using the Service as a means.(10) Deleting or changing product display, copyright notice, other cautionary statements, or restrictions based on property rights.(11) Duplication, delivery, public transmission, modification, translation, adaption, or producing derivative works.(12) Relocation, sell, transfer, or doing other dispositions to the third party.(13) Let the third party use the Service regardless of licensing, lending or other means.(14) Doing acts of analysis, such as reverse-engineering, etc.(15) Obstructing the operation of the Service, or discrediting the Service, or doing acts that may disturb or damage the Service.(16) Acts which the Company deems inappropriate, or acts that may be inappropriate..Article 8 (Cautions and Warnings on Usage).General rules.(1) The provision of the Service may not be received due to radio wave reception status by an information terminal to be used (hereinafter referred to as “the Information Terminal”), functional restrictions of the Information Terminal, or settings of the Information Terminal by the customer.(2) A map, route, facility, etc. on the Service may be different from actual information, or contents may not be accurate. In addition, the Service information may be changed without notification to the customer.(3) Of the countries or regions to be covered by the Service, the provision of the Service information cannot be received in a part of the locations.(4)